# BASELINE REPRODUCTION: Complex String Concatenation and Escaping
# Validates parser's ability to handle highly dense and convoluted strings
# frequently found in command-line arguments being parsed.
# The tool MUST not throw syntax errors on unbalanced quotes within properly escaped strings.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: The field `cmdline` correctly maps to the complex string.
filter {
  mutate {
    add_field => {
      "cmdline" => "cmd.exe /c \"echo \\\"Hello World\\\" && dir C:\\Windows\\System32\""
      "escaped_quote_field" => "This is a literal quote: \""
    }
  }
}
